<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="182" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d182">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName>
                                to Prime Minister <persName type="to">Churchill</persName>
                            </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d182fn1">Sent to the United States Naval
                                Attaché London, via Navy channels.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-25">July 25, 1943</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Number 325 for the <gloss target="#t_FNP1">Former Naval Person</gloss>
                            from the President personal and secret.</p>
                        <p>I am perfectly delighted. I wish much that <gloss target="#t_LW1">Lady
                                Warden</gloss> and her daughter and the Colonel could come to Hyde
                            Park on arrival as my wife leaves on a month’s inspection trip on the
                            15th. If they cannot come then I would hope for a visit later in
                            August.</p>
                        <pb facs="0514" n="400" xml:id="pg_400"/>
                        <p>The Staffs can begin their work at <gloss target="#t_Abraham1">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Abraham</hi>
                            </gloss> before the 17th and I will let you have a definite date
                            shortly.</p>
                        <p>I hope to go on a short trip to fish and sleep next Saturday.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>